			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Molto Espressivo Wins All Bard LDoN Mission, lvl 49 - 56<a name="21380"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 04 10:54 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Molto Espressivo, the All Bard Guild on Firiona Vie server started as an experiment in all bard grouping with bards from the old eqdiva EZboards.  Originally, I just wanted 5 other people to play with me once a week, and we would level together and see what we could do.
<br />

<br />
It exploded into a whole guild.  We have trimmed the roster several times of inactive bard when it got over 100.  Right now, we have 75 on the roster, about half of those play very regularly as mains.
<br />

<br />
Well, we took all bard groups into many places where people would normally think that only a &quot;balanced group&quot; would dare to tread.  Obviously, we OWN outdoor zones, hehe.  But what about dungeons?
<br />

<br />
Before LDoN, we took a group of lvl 23 - 31 Bards into Splitpaw and kicked a$.  Once LDoN came out, we did all bard groups in our 40s and won missions without too much trouble.
<br />

<br />
I was beginning to think, however, that 50+ was just going to be too tough.  We hadn't tried it in a while, but last night we did a Mistmoor collection mission with 5 bards, levels 49 - 56.  We kicked a$.  No one died, and we won the mission with 36 minutes to spare.
<br />

<br />
How did we do it?  We didn't even have to kite in any way either!  I was pulling and Chant-Tanking (I'm the 56).  Conga used his TDoK and Vampire's Lute of Bone, and twisted Nillipus, Shield of Songs, and Heal.  The other three meleed.  Stretto staggered his rune songs, and did Nillipus, SoS, and Battlecry of the Vah Shir.  Cantilena did Snare, Verses of Victory, and... I forget, lol.  Denben did Kattas and Amped a Psalm DS, iirc.
<br />

<br />
I either pulled singles, or charm pulled pairs.  When I got down below 40% or so, I fired up Nivs for the added HP regen, (Stretto stopped SoS-- no stackie), and Conga kept heal on while I sat down with my lute for a quick breather.  Downtime was minimal, however.
<br />

<br />
Oh yeah, on casters, Conga and I kept up our roles, while others chain mezzed em.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Scherzo Glissando <BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
