				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Molto Espressivo Wins All Bard LDoN Mission, lvl 49 - 56<a name="21466"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 15 04 4:31 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>It was spectacular.  With Shield of Songs refreshing  on Scherzo/Klapton almost every time he got hit and HP regen going in the background, he actually GAINED health on some fights.  Most fights he lost something like 2-5% HP, gaining some back during the pull.  
<br />

<br />
By the time we succeeded, Scherzo had never been below 40% health, none of the rest of us were ever below 90% I think.  We did it in just under an hour.  We decided to continue to XP for the remaining 30 min and during that time he got down to 30% one time.
<br />

<br />
Playing in Molto, thinking in different ways about how to use multiple bards, has given me insight on how to be a better bard when grouped with other classes.  The knowledge of bard stacking and combination has made me kind of the expert in my main's guild for bard coordination.  I don't full time with Molto, nor even close to it, but the exposure has made me and friends better bards
<br />

<br />
There are several variations on what we did that have my mind racing, but it was thrilling to be a part of it
<br />

<br />
Stretto / Reys</span></td>
