				<td colspan="2"><span>Well, to be honest, I think a very skilled swarming Bard might solo an LDoN slaughter as well, hehe.  The only really tough thing would be dealing with casters.  The solution, of course, is to charm the casters first.
<br />

<br />
There are several other tactics we want to try.  AE kiting whole rooms, for example.  One RS3 Bard would pull, do the highest dmg songs to draw aggro, and do tight AE circles.  The rest would simply stand among the mobs twisting CoD, any other stacking AEs, and rune and regen songs to absorb boo boos.
<br />

<br />
We have also done Chant/Snare Aggro drags in Rajukan.  We only had 4 bards on that one, and we didn't have quite the DPS to finish in time.  Of course, snare-dragging them means no damage, thus no downtime.  With 5 or 6 Bards, this would work np.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%">Scherzo Glissando <BR>
