			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Molto Espressivo Wins All Bard LDoN Mission, lvl 49 - 56<a name="21915"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 17 04 2:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>That would work to a point...I deal with 65 dungeons though, and the mobs are too high to swarm.
<br />

<br />
AE kiting could work, but casters are more of a problem for that than for swarming.  
<br />

<br />
Generally the best strategy I've heard for multiple bards to kill stuff quick is ghetto-AE, but generally that requires a cleric and chanter for group heals/stuns.  If you have everyone twisting in runes at different points in their twists it might succeed. 
<br />

<br />
I'd recommend having everyone do (using best lute of course):
<br />
CoD
<br />
DDD
<br />
MoM (if they have it) or Selo's Chords of Cessation
<br />

<br />
Have one person do Selo's Assonant Strane - best AE slow % and adds snare.  Not sure stacking though.
<br />

<br />
And everyone else should do a Regen or rune song - probably &gt;1 doing SoS / Nillipuss.
<br />

<br />
If you drop a song with 6 bards it isn't a huge deal, so have everyone try 4-twisting even if they're not great at it.  If not, drop DDD if they don't have epic, since it's brass instead of lute the dmg stinks unless you instrument swap.
<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
